HEADWORD: Galvanoscope
<hw>Gal*van`o*scope</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Galvanic</ets> + <ets>-scope</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>galvanoscope</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>An instrument or
apparatus for detecting the presence of electrical currents, especially
such as are of feeble intensity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Galvanoscopic</ent>⟦br⟧
